        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions MRL 2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, fluid viscosity, temperature) documented and traceable to FDA GCBP test protocol. Boundary condition uncertainty quantified and reported."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA GCBP experimental test conditions are fully documented in the published protocol. Inlet flow rates (2–6 L/min), rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM), and fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture at 37°C) are traceable to calibrated measurement equipment with stated uncertainties, satisfying MRL 2 test conditions requirements."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-nc2/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
