      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-nc2/relevance-qoi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoI MRL 2 acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Quantities of interest (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) are directly linked to clinical hemolysis outcomes and regulatory acceptance criteria for CPB devices."
      },
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI and is directly referenced in FDA guidance for CPB device evaluation. Shear stress scalar stress is the mechanistic driver of hemolysis in the power-law model. Both QoIs are well-established in the blood pump simulation literature and directly relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
